Forced browsing is when attackers directly access URLs or API endpoints they're not authorized to view, often by guessing or enumerating resource identifiers. The 2022 Optus breach exposed 9.8 million records because attackers could simply increment customer IDs to access any customer's data without authorization checks.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```go
